data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a group of people who are chosen, usually by a larger group, to make decisions or to deal with a particular subject

data.chText: 委员会已决定关闭这家餐馆。
data.enText: The committee has/have decided to close the restaurant.
a committee member/a member of the committee

tr: a special group delegated to consider some matter
example: a committee is a group that keeps minutes and loses hours" - Milton Berl

tr: a self-constituted organization to promote something

value.def: A committee is a group of people who meet to make decisions or plans for a larger group or organization that they represent.

example.ex: ...an elected Management Committee who serve the Association on a voluntary basis.
example.tran: 通过选举产生、自愿为协会服务的管理委员会

example.ex: My reasons were stated in writing and circulated to all committee members.
example.tran: 我提出的几个理由以书面形式呈现，在所有委员会成员中传阅。

trans: 政治行动委员会(美国组织，为所支持的公职候选人筹集资金)
特别委员会(为研究某课题等而成立)
(运动队队员等的)选拔委员会，遴选委员会
